\section{Agriculture in GCAM}
GCAM is comprehensively described elsewhere \citep[e.g.][]{}. A summary of the land system component of GCAM is provided here for the sake of completeness. The land component of GCAM divides the terrestrial system into 283 subregions based on the intersection of 32 geopolitical regions with 18 agroecological zones. The model simulates the area of five natural land cover types and 17 managed land cover types, of which several are involved in the production of 11 agricultural commodities \citep{}. The initial area of managed land cover types and associated production of commodities in each of the 32 mondel regions is obtained from the FAOSTAT database \citep{}. These values are disaggregated to the various agro-ecological zones using production and area shares from the the Global Trade Analysis Project (GTAP) model \citep{}. In future time steps GCAM simulates the area and production of managed land cover types on the basis of various drivers including food demand, costs associated with agricultural production and demand for bioenergy, amongst others. \\

