\section{Model evaluation}

To evaluate the algorithm we use it to downscale historical crop production values for India during the period 1970--2010, and compared the simulated output with historical maps from a spatio-temporal dataset showing the evolution of irrigated and rainfed crops during the same period \citep{moulds2018}. The initial condition for the downscaling algorithm is provided by the crop distribution maps for 1960, with maps for subsequent time points used for comparison. We obtain regional production values for India by multiplying the crop area maps by corresponding yield maps. \\

